cs.SE, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CY 

This paper discusses the trustworthiness of cyber-physical systems (CPS) and proposes an ontology-based approach to reason about CPS. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SE (Software Engineering) as it deals with the design, development, and maintenance of software systems. The paper also discusses security issues related to CPS, which makes cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) another likely category. The use of ontology and reasoning techniques suggests that the paper could also fit into cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) categories. Finally, the paper's focus on the integration of cyber and physical systems makes cs.CY (Computers and Society) a possible category as well.
